937
01:10:35,215 --> 01:10:36,807
So many repeats.

938
01:10:37,851 --> 01:10:39,648
Eat the steak, and then get a pen.

939
01:10:44,024 --> 01:10:47,016
"Did man fall from grace
in the Garden of Eden?"

940
01:10:48,362 --> 01:10:52,298
I'll tell you something, never came out.
I made Adam 17.

941
01:10:52,499 --> 01:10:54,990
Eve was 15, 16, tops.

942
01:10:55,369 --> 01:10:58,463
I figured then,
16, 17 was middle-age, you know.

943
01:10:58,539 --> 01:11:03,067
Who knew people would live so long?
Trees, I figured they had the best chance.

944
01:11:03,143 --> 01:11:05,976
Now I realize that they were kids, babies.

945
01:11:06,080 --> 01:11:10,380
Young people can't fall from my grace.
They're my best things. Put that down.

946
01:11:14,555 --> 01:11:16,682
- "Which of the world's..."
- Wait.

947
01:11:18,192 --> 01:11:19,192
Okay.

948
01:11:19,259 --> 01:11:23,320
"Which of the world's religions is
the closest to the divine truth?"

949
01:11:24,198 --> 01:11:27,895
The divine truth is not in a building
or a book or a story.

950
01:11:29,003 --> 01:11:32,962
Put down that the heart is the temple
wherein all truth resides.

951
01:11:36,276 --> 01:11:38,710
"Is Jesus Christ the son of God?"

952
01:11:45,686 --> 01:11:46,983
Jesus was my son.

953
01:11:49,023 --> 01:11:50,547
Buddha was my son.

954
01:11:51,091 --> 01:11:53,719
Mohammed, Moses, you...

955
01:11:53,861 --> 01:11:57,262
the man who said there was
no room in the inn was my son.

956
01:11:57,331 --> 01:12:00,528
So is the one who charges $11 for steak
in this one.

957
01:12:00,601 --> 01:12:02,034
Let's mush on.

958
01:12:02,536 --> 01:12:04,663
What was that last question?

959
01:12:07,307 --> 01:12:10,674
- "Will there..."
- "Will there be a judgment day for man?"

960
01:12:12,446 --> 01:12:15,847
If they mean a doomsday,
an end-of-the-world thing...

961
01:12:15,916 --> 01:12:18,077
I'm certainly not going to get into that.

962
01:12:18,152 --> 01:12:21,883
But if you want my personal opinion,
I wouldn't look forward to it.

963
01:12:21,955 --> 01:12:25,413
There'd be a lot of yelling,
and I don't need that anymore than you do.

964
01:12:25,492 --> 01:12:26,720
Got that?

965
01:12:27,561 --> 01:12:28,721
Got it.

966
01:12:29,363 --> 01:12:32,332
"What is the meaning of man's existence?"

967
01:12:34,935 --> 01:12:36,835
Life is like a glass of tea.

968
01:12:38,005 --> 01:12:42,942
No, I better not go for laughs.
Voltaire may have had me pegged, right?

969
01:12:43,577 --> 01:12:47,741
He said I was a comedian playing
to an audience who's afraid to laugh.

970
01:12:47,915 --> 01:12:51,442
But seriously,
put down that man and women-persons...

971
01:12:52,219 --> 01:12:55,518
their existence means
exactly and precisely...

972
01:12:55,589 --> 01:12:59,047
not more, not one tiny bit less,
just what they think it means.

973
01:12:59,126 --> 01:13:01,560
What I think doesn't count at all.

974
01:13:02,396 --> 01:13:05,388
- That's very profound.
- Sometimes I get lucky.

975
01:13:08,235 --> 01:13:10,465
- Last question.
- Thank God.

976
01:13:10,537 --> 01:13:11,936
You're welcome.

977
01:13:13,207 --> 01:13:16,074
"Why have you chosen
to appear at this time?"

978
01:13:16,543 --> 01:13:18,010
You've already said.

979
01:13:18,078 --> 01:13:20,239
Maybe they want to hear it
in your own words.

980
01:13:21,882 --> 01:13:25,841
I want to say to everyone that everything
around them that they see and smell...

981
01:13:25,919 --> 01:13:28,717
and feel and hear,
they should delight in all this.

982
01:13:28,789 --> 01:13:31,781
That what is here are
some of my very best ideas.

983
01:13:31,859 --> 01:13:33,554
I want everyone to try very hard...

984
01:13:33,627 --> 01:13:36,118
to make sure
it doesn't all go down the drain.

985
01:13:37,164 --> 01:13:39,325
Give me, I'll do it.

986
01:13:42,436 --> 01:13:45,894
Can you remember exactly what you said?
It was perfect.

987
01:13:48,575 --> 01:13:51,601
Boy, these answers are
really going to get them.

988
01:13:53,380 --> 01:13:54,972
That's my handwriting!

989
01:13:55,682 --> 01:13:57,149
Imagine that.

990
01:13:58,552 --> 01:14:00,679
Shall I call the panel
and tell them I'm ready?

991
01:14:00,754 --> 01:14:04,053
Never mind the panel.
You deliver those papers to Rev. Williams...

992
01:14:04,124 --> 01:14:07,321
- the one who looks like a football player.
- I didn't like him.

993
01:14:07,394 --> 01:14:10,488
He's having one of his big dos
at the Shrine Auditorium.

994
01:14:10,564 --> 01:14:14,125
Every time I turn around,
he's spreading the word, my word.

995
01:14:14,201 --> 01:14:18,103
Only, my words he ran out of years ago.
I'll tell you the truth.

996
01:14:19,106 --> 01:14:21,040
The reason I put everybody here naked...

997
01:14:21,108 --> 01:14:25,306
I wasn't trying to be cute,
I just didn't want to create clothes.

998
01:14:25,379 --> 01:14:29,645
With clothes, there's right away pockets,
and you have to put something in them.

999
01:14:29,716 --> 01:14:31,980
You take these,
and give them to Rev. Bigmouth.

1000
01:14:32,052 --> 01:14:34,577
Tell him that God says he's a phony.

1001
01:14:34,855 --> 01:14:38,621
Also, tell him if he wants to get rich, fine.
Tell him to sell Earth Shoes.

1002
01:14:38,692 --> 01:14:42,560
But personally tell him
I'd like him to shut up. I'll see you.

1003
01:14:46,733 --> 01:14:47,859
God?

1004
01:14:49,536 --> 01:14:50,662
Yeah?

1005
01:14:51,438 --> 01:14:54,305
- Thank you.
- Hope I get an "A."

1006
01:14:59,079 --> 01:15:00,307
<i>Love.</i>

1007
01:15:01,281 --> 01:15:03,306
<i>Let's talk about love.</i>

1008
01:15:04,518 --> 01:15:05,678
<i>What is it?</i>

1009
01:15:06,153 --> 01:15:08,849
<i>You can love your brother, can't you?</i>

1010
01:15:09,223 --> 01:15:12,192
<i>You can love your wife or your husband.</i>

1011
01:15:13,860 --> 01:15:15,953
<i>You can love your new dress.</i>

1012
01:15:16,496 --> 01:15:18,464
<i>You can love my new car.</i>

1013
01:15:20,434 --> 01:15:22,664
<i>You can pass by a pet shop...</i>

1014
01:15:23,103 --> 01:15:26,630
<i>and say, "I just love
that little doggie in the window,"</i>

1015
01:15:27,941 --> 01:15:30,705
<i>You can love this, and you can love that.</i>

1016
01:15:31,445 --> 01:15:33,640
<i>But what am I talking about?</i>

1017
01:15:34,748 --> 01:15:36,579
<i>Some folks say...</i>

1018
01:15:36,650 --> 01:15:40,313
<i>that love is what they saw
in a pornographic movie.</i>

1019
01:15:41,421 --> 01:15:44,254
<i>But that is lust, not love.</i>

1020
01:15:46,360 --> 01:15:49,261
<i>- Is that what you want?</i>
- No!

1021
01:15:49,763 --> 01:15:52,061
<i>- Is that love?</i>
- No!

1022
01:15:52,132 --> 01:15:55,101
<i>- Is that what the Bible teaches?</i>
- No!

1023
01:15:55,168 --> 01:15:57,728
<i>- Is that what I'm talking about?</i>
- No!

1024
01:15:57,838 --> 01:16:01,535
<i>No, because what I'm talking about
is the kind of love...</i>

1025
01:16:01,608 --> 01:16:04,168
<i>that calls for a sacrifice.</i>

1026
01:16:05,812 --> 01:16:08,440
<i>Are you willing to make a sacrifice...</i>

1027
01:16:08,515 --> 01:16:11,245
<i>to show God how much you love him?</i>

1028
01:16:11,318 --> 01:16:12,444
Yes!

1029
01:16:12,519 --> 01:16:16,888
<i>To show God how you love him
with all of your heart and soul?</i>

1030
01:16:17,424 --> 01:16:18,424
Yes!

1031
01:16:18,992 --> 01:16:21,756
<i>- How do we love God? With all our...</i>
- Hearts!

1032
01:16:21,828 --> 01:16:24,695
<i>- How do we love God? With all our...</i>
- Souls!

1033
01:16:24,765 --> 01:16:27,529
<i>- Is that what I'm talking about?</i>
- Yes!

1034
01:16:28,702 --> 01:16:30,693
<i>Yes, amen, I say, yes!</i>

1035
01:16:30,771 --> 01:16:33,899
<i>- Raise your right hand, and say amen!</i>
- Amen!

1036
01:16:33,974 --> 01:16:35,532
<i>- Say amen!</i>
- Amen!

1037
01:16:43,617 --> 01:16:46,780
<i>And you can show God how you love him...</i>

1038
01:16:48,388 --> 01:16:50,413
<i>by digging down deep...</i>

1039
01:16:52,125 --> 01:16:57,119
<i>so that this ministry will reach
all of the people of the earth!</i>

1040
01:16:57,564 --> 01:16:59,725
<i>Because the Bible tells us:</i>

1041
01:16:59,800 --> 01:17:03,668
<i>"Show God you love him,
and he will show you the way,"</i>

1042
01:17:04,137 --> 01:17:05,399
Amen!

1043
01:17:06,006 --> 01:17:08,804
<i>Now, I'm going to ask all of you
to come up.</i>

1044
01:17:09,176 --> 01:17:11,167
<i>Those of you who haven't come up before...</i>

1045
01:17:11,244 --> 01:17:14,179
<i>I'm going to ask you to come up for God.</i>

1046
01:17:14,981 --> 01:17:19,611
<i>Shake my hand, and let God see us together.</i>

1047
01:17:20,787 --> 01:17:23,483
<i>Because the Bible tells us...</i>

1048
01:17:23,557 --> 01:17:26,958
<i>that God knows the falling of a sparrow...</i>

1049
01:17:27,594 --> 01:17:32,588
<i>and the depth of a pocket,
and that is what I'm talking about!</i>

1050
01:17:32,799 --> 01:17:33,993
Amen!

1051
01:17:35,168 --> 01:17:38,399
<i>Come up, brothers and sisters...</i>

1052
01:17:38,672 --> 01:17:43,405
<i>and put in our hands
what you would put in God's hands...</i>

1053
01:17:43,610 --> 01:17:48,274
<i>and he will have the whole world
in his hands!</i>

1054
01:17:50,016 --> 01:17:54,578
"He's got the whole world in his hands

1055
01:17:54,654 --> 01:17:58,715
"He's got the whole world in his hands

1056
01:17:58,792 --> 01:18:02,751
"He's got the whole world in his hands

1057
01:18:02,829 --> 01:18:04,626
"He's got the whole world..."

1058
01:18:04,698 --> 01:18:07,360
May the Lord bless and keep you.
It's so good to see you.

1059
01:18:07,434 --> 01:18:08,492
You can put that right...

1060
01:18:08,568 --> 01:18:11,036
Yes, thank you very much. God bless you.

1061
01:18:12,706 --> 01:18:16,142
May the Lord always bless you
and keep you. It's so good to see you.

1062
01:18:16,209 --> 01:18:17,836
Thank you, please keep moving.

1063
01:18:18,912 --> 01:18:20,903
- Rev. Williams.
- That's all right.

1064
01:18:20,981 --> 01:18:23,006
He is in need of me.
What are you doing here?

1065
01:18:23,083 --> 01:18:25,847
- God sent me to you.
- One moment!

1066
01:18:27,954 --> 01:18:31,583
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
brothers and sisters...</i>

1067
01:18:32,125 --> 01:18:36,425
<i>this is the young man
who has used so much energy...</i>

1068
01:18:36,496 --> 01:18:40,489
<i>to convince everyone that he has seen God.</i>

1069
01:18:42,302 --> 01:18:43,360
<i>Now, wait!</i>

1070
01:18:45,539 --> 01:18:47,837
<i>Would you repeat what you just said to me?</i>

1071
01:18:49,509 --> 01:18:50,771
<i>God sent me to you.</i>

1072
01:18:51,311 --> 01:18:54,747
<i>God sent him to me!</i>

1073
01:18:56,016 --> 01:18:59,110
<i>- Are you certain of that?
- Yes, I just left him.</i>

1074
01:19:00,387 --> 01:19:04,380
<i>He wanted me to give you these answers
to all of those questions.</i>

1075
01:19:04,458 --> 01:19:06,551
<i>- God specified me?
- Yes.</i>

1076
01:19:06,860 --> 01:19:10,023
<i>And he also asked me to tell you
that he's very unhappy.</i>

1077
01:19:10,096 --> 01:19:12,826
<i>God is very unhappy.</i>

1078
01:19:12,899 --> 01:19:17,393
<i>Yes, he's unhappy that you're
getting rich this way.</i>

1079
01:19:17,471 --> 01:19:21,464
<i>And that he'd like you to stop pretending
that you're spreading his word.</i>

1080
01:19:21,741 --> 01:19:24,209
<i>In fact, he suggested that you sell shoes.</i>

1081
01:19:25,512 --> 01:19:27,742
That's what he said! You're a fake!

1082
01:19:28,748 --> 01:19:30,773
<i>This poor boy is ill.</i>

1083
01:19:30,917 --> 01:19:32,179
Get him out of here!

1084
01:19:35,222 --> 01:19:36,883
Rev. Williams!

1085
01:19:38,925 --> 01:19:42,986
Slander, Your Honor.
Slander, surely, cruel and foul.

1086
01:19:44,130 --> 01:19:47,531
The Rev. Willie Williams is
on the road for God...

1087
01:19:47,601 --> 01:19:50,126
to the tune of 100,000 miles a year.

1088
01:19:50,637 --> 01:19:53,731
He's a tireless, selfless
servant of the Lord.

1089
01:19:54,674 --> 01:19:59,668
The idea that he'd line his pockets
in this pursuit is the unkindest cut of all.

1090
01:20:00,947 --> 01:20:03,882
Not only is Willie Williams'
organization nonprofit...

1091
01:20:03,950 --> 01:20:08,649
he personally pays over six figures
in income tax every year.

1092
01:20:09,022 --> 01:20:11,547
Give him back his honor, Your Honor.

1093
01:20:12,359 --> 01:20:16,819
Award him the damages we seek
from this defendant.

1094
01:20:18,465 --> 01:20:20,558
A man so out of touch with reality...

1095
01:20:20,634 --> 01:20:24,502
he even tries to smear the good name
of a religious giant.

1096
01:20:24,905 --> 01:20:28,773
A man whom the President of
the United States once called...

1097
01:20:28,842 --> 01:20:31,072
"God's own quarterback."

1098
01:20:33,280 --> 01:20:35,043
Thank you, Your Honor.

1099
01:20:38,485 --> 01:20:41,579
Mr. Landers, will you come
to the bench, please?

1100
01:20:46,993 --> 01:20:49,621
- You haven't changed your mind?
- No, sir.

1101
01:20:49,930 --> 01:20:54,594
A professional lawyer would be helpful.
This is a tough time for you to be alone.

1102
01:20:56,169 --> 01:20:58,637
I won't be alone, sir.

1103
01:21:05,345 --> 01:21:08,610
- They're just going to kill you today, Jerry.
- We'll see.

1104
01:21:09,115 --> 01:21:12,107
We're going to lose everything
you worked for.

1105
01:21:14,054 --> 01:21:16,420
Isn't there any way
you can say you're sorry?

1106
01:21:16,489 --> 01:21:18,252
That it was all a big mistake?

1107
01:21:18,825 --> 01:21:22,124
No, because I'm not, and it wasn't.

1108
01:21:22,963 --> 01:21:25,625
I just can't believe
that God would set me up...

1109
01:21:25,699 --> 01:21:28,099
<i>to get me into all of this trouble.</i>

1110
01:21:28,168 --> 01:21:30,898
<i>I have to believe that he had a reason...</i>

1111
01:21:30,971 --> 01:21:34,907
<i>and I have to believe
that he'll bail me out.</i>

1112
01:21:35,275 --> 01:21:39,575
<i>And all I want to say is,
that young man is out of his mind.</i>

1113
01:21:40,480 --> 01:21:45,213
And the absolute being, the all-powerful,
all-knowing, all-merciful...

1114
01:21:45,285 --> 01:21:48,448
infinite spirit, the supreme soul...

1115
01:21:48,521 --> 01:21:50,955
the King of Kings, and Lord of Lords...

1116
01:21:51,591 --> 01:21:54,719
the infinite, everlasting eternal being...

1117
01:21:55,295 --> 01:21:58,389
last came to you how?

1118
01:22:00,433 --> 01:22:01,798
As a busboy.

1119
01:22:08,475 --> 01:22:10,739
Your Honor, I rest my case.

1120
01:22:15,649 --> 01:22:17,913
You may step down now, Mr. Landers.

1121
01:22:26,259 --> 01:22:29,057
Call your witnesses, please, Mr. Landers.

1122
01:22:29,262 --> 01:22:33,198
Yes, Your Honor, I would like to call
one witness and one witness only.

1123
01:22:42,142 --> 01:22:43,871
I'm waiting, Mr. Landers.

1124
01:22:45,278 --> 01:22:46,336
Yes.

1125
01:22:48,682 --> 01:22:53,119
Your Honor, I would like to call
to the stand the Lord God.

1126
01:22:57,257 --> 01:23:01,159
I object. The defendant's trying
to make a mockery of this proceeding.

1127
01:23:01,394 --> 01:23:03,487
Your Honor, I was trying to make a point.

1128
01:23:03,563 --> 01:23:05,463
- What point?
- Your Honor...

1129
01:23:08,768 --> 01:23:11,794
when I just asked God to take the stand...

1130
01:23:12,472 --> 01:23:17,239
in that brief moment after I called him,
wasn't there a trace of expectation?

1131
01:23:17,444 --> 01:23:19,309
Just a trace, Your Honor?

1132
01:23:20,747 --> 01:23:24,444
Wasn't there a hesitation in this room?
Didn't you feel it?

1133
01:23:27,220 --> 01:23:29,051
Didn't we all feel it?

1134
01:23:30,623 --> 01:23:33,820
It was the possibility that God does exist.

1135
01:23:34,094 --> 01:23:38,326
And if he exists, he could materialize
and sit right in that chair.

1136
01:23:39,299 --> 01:23:42,757
In that moment, Your Honor,
when no one in this room knew...

1137
01:23:42,836 --> 01:23:46,363
what was going to happen next,
in that flash of an instant...

1138
01:23:46,740 --> 01:23:51,200
lies the benefit of the doubt you must
give me to know that my story is true.

1139
01:23:51,277 --> 01:23:54,178
And that I spoke exactly as God asked me.

1140
01:23:55,515 --> 01:24:00,475
Mr. Landers, I cautioned you earlier
that legal representation would be helpful.

1141
01:24:01,221 --> 01:24:04,452
I must now warn you that,
in addition to the plaintiff's charges...

1142
01:24:04,524 --> 01:24:07,084
I'm seriously considering
citing you with contempt.

1143
01:24:07,160 --> 01:24:08,160
Amen.

1144
01:24:08,228 --> 01:24:11,095
For what you apparently thought
was a very clever stunt.

1145
01:24:11,164 --> 01:24:15,225
You're getting deeper and deeper
into trouble with this court, Mr. Landers.

1146
01:24:15,301 --> 01:24:16,825
Excuse me, Your Honor.

1147
01:24:20,039 --> 01:24:21,165
It's him.

1148
01:24:23,042 --> 01:24:24,441
Bobbie, it's him.

1149
01:24:27,514 --> 01:24:30,039
- This is most irregular.
- Your Honor, he...

1150
01:24:30,116 --> 01:24:31,708
I'll take it from here.

1151
01:24:33,052 --> 01:24:35,179
May I ask who you are, sir?

1152
01:24:35,255 --> 01:24:38,349
You better swear me in.
You'll never believe it.

1153
01:24:47,066 --> 01:24:50,627
Do you swear to tell the truth,
the whole truth, and nothing but the truth?

1154
01:24:50,703 --> 01:24:52,227
So help me me.

1155
01:24:53,039 --> 01:24:54,597
So help you you?

1156
01:24:55,975 --> 01:24:59,604
If it pleases the court,
and even if it doesn't please the court...

1157
01:24:59,679 --> 01:25:01,613
I'm God, Your Honor.

1158
01:25:07,120 --> 01:25:08,747
Order in the court.

1159
01:25:10,690 --> 01:25:14,854
Your Honor, I'd like permission
to question this witness.

1160
01:25:15,228 --> 01:25:18,322
Sit down, Sonny,
I've answered enough questions.

1161
01:25:22,969 --> 01:25:27,201
He saw me, just like he said.
Each word true.

1162
01:25:28,374 --> 01:25:31,810
The man tried to tell a lie,
his tongue would snap off.

1163
01:25:32,345 --> 01:25:35,439
Which I wouldn't say
I could say about everybody.

1164
01:25:35,515 --> 01:25:37,540
Why is it so hard for you to believe?

1165
01:25:37,617 --> 01:25:41,053
Is my physical existence
any more improbable than your own?

1166
01:25:42,288 --> 01:25:45,655
What about all that hoo-hah with the devil
a while ago, from that movie?

1167
01:25:45,725 --> 01:25:48,319
Nobody had trouble believing
that the devil took over...

1168
01:25:48,394 --> 01:25:50,692
and existed in the little girl.

1169
01:25:50,930 --> 01:25:52,693
All she had to do was wet the rug...

1170
01:25:52,765 --> 01:25:55,893
throw up some pea soup,
and everybody believed.

1171
01:25:57,103 --> 01:25:59,833
The devil you could believe, but not God?

1172
01:26:01,207 --> 01:26:04,870
I work in my own way.
I don't get inside little children.

1173
01:26:05,445 --> 01:26:08,312
They got enough to do,
just being themselves.

1174
01:26:09,148 --> 01:26:12,117
I'm not going to go around
to every person in the world and say:

1175
01:26:12,185 --> 01:26:14,619
"Look, it's me, I want to talk to you."

1176
01:26:14,888 --> 01:26:16,549
So I picked one man.

1177
01:26:18,157 --> 01:26:19,818
One very good man.

1178
01:26:21,828 --> 01:26:24,626
I told him God lives. I live.

1179
01:26:26,199 --> 01:26:30,761
He had trouble believing, too,
in the beginning. I understood.

1180
01:26:33,006 --> 01:26:36,100
I'm not sure how
this whole miracle business started.

1181
01:26:36,175 --> 01:26:40,077
The idea that anything connected with me
has to be a miracle.

1182
01:26:40,780 --> 01:26:42,714
Personally, I'm sorry that it did.

1183
01:26:42,782 --> 01:26:45,751
It makes the distance between us
even greater.

1184
01:26:47,687 --> 01:26:51,748
But if a miracle helps you believe
that I am who I say I am...

1185
01:26:54,961 --> 01:26:57,054
I'll give you one, a good one.

1186
01:26:57,864 --> 01:27:01,732
Let me see.
What's my most impressive miracle?

1187
01:27:07,140 --> 01:27:08,835
Pick a card.

1188
01:27:09,008 --> 01:27:12,500
- What?
- Pick a card, any card.

1189
01:27:15,949 --> 01:27:20,886
- I don't know what you think you're doing.
- A cute little miracle. Go ahead, pick one.

1190
01:27:21,087 --> 01:27:23,783
- There are no cards there.
- Look again.

1191
01:27:30,463 --> 01:27:32,931
There's nothing miraculous
about good sleight of hand.

1192
01:27:32,999 --> 01:27:35,126
Have you ever seen this one?

1193
01:27:43,543 --> 01:27:47,946
Yes, I've seen them make cards appear
and disappear.

1194
01:27:50,683 --> 01:27:54,084
As a matter of fact, I once saw
a magician make an elephant disappear.

1195
01:27:54,420 --> 01:27:57,617
Good. Now I'll show you one
that you haven't seen.

1196
01:28:01,094 --> 01:28:03,221
Have to get these shoes fixed.

1197
01:28:05,832 --> 01:28:08,198
Watch this, Your Honor.

1198
01:28:27,453 --> 01:28:30,718
<i>I know how hard it is, in these times,
to have faith.</i>

1199
01:28:31,290 --> 01:28:34,657
<i>But maybe if you could have the faith
to start with...</i>

1200
01:28:34,894 --> 01:28:39,831
<i>maybe the times would change.
You could change them, Think about it.</i>

1201
01:28:40,767 --> 01:28:43,736
<i>Try, And try not to hurt each other.</i>

1202
01:28:44,537 --> 01:28:46,664
<i>There's been enough of that.</i>

1203
01:28:47,106 --> 01:28:49,131
<i>It really gets in the way.</i>

1204
01:28:49,709 --> 01:28:53,440
<i>I'm a God of very few words,
and Jerry's already given you mine.</i>

1205
01:28:54,747 --> 01:28:58,740
<i>However hopeless, helpless,
mixed-up and scary it all gets...</i>

1206
01:28:59,719 --> 01:29:01,209
<i>it can work.</i>

1207
01:29:01,988 --> 01:29:04,422
<i>If you find it hard to believe in me...</i>

1208
01:29:04,590 --> 01:29:08,151
<i>maybe it would help you to know
that I believe in you.</i>

1209
01:29:08,828 --> 01:29:10,853
<i>Your Honor, I rest my case.</i>

1210
01:29:23,843 --> 01:29:25,037
What?

1211
01:29:31,851 --> 01:29:34,251
This court is now recessed.

1212
01:29:36,322 --> 01:29:39,485
May I see both parties
in my chambers, please?

1213
01:29:40,026 --> 01:29:43,860
<i>Do you swear to tell the truth,
the whole truth and nothing but the truth?</i>

1214
01:29:44,564 --> 01:29:46,156
<i>So help you you?</i>

1215
01:29:48,634 --> 01:29:49,862
Where's...

1216
01:29:53,539 --> 01:29:55,200
<i>Order in the court.</i>

1217
01:29:56,976 --> 01:30:01,310
<i>Your Honor, I'd like permission
to question this witness.</i>

1218
01:30:11,424 --> 01:30:13,221
That's all there is.

1219
01:30:13,559 --> 01:30:18,428
Not one word of what I assume
we all assume we heard.

1220
01:30:18,498 --> 01:30:20,056
Someone must have erased it.

1221
01:30:22,635 --> 01:30:25,126
Nobody erases tapes anymore.

1222
01:30:26,539 --> 01:30:30,100
- Then the machine...
- No. Not a thing wrong with it.

1223
01:30:31,444 --> 01:30:33,776
He said he couldn't be recorded.

1224
01:30:33,846 --> 01:30:38,283
God, when he first spoke to me,
he said it wasn't his real voice I heard.

1225
01:30:38,351 --> 01:30:41,115
He said he was just using one
that I could understand.

1226
01:30:41,187 --> 01:30:42,916
He did it again today.

1227
01:30:42,989 --> 01:30:45,787
And there's nothing wrong
with your stenotype machine?

1228
01:30:45,858 --> 01:30:48,850
It took down every word, Your Honor,
except now...

1229
01:30:48,928 --> 01:30:51,192
some of them are not on the paper.

1230
01:30:51,531 --> 01:30:54,864
Don't you see?
He wants us all to decide for ourselves...

1231
01:30:54,934 --> 01:30:56,993
whether or not we saw him and heard him.

1232
01:30:57,069 --> 01:31:00,197
It's what he always said,
that everything is up to us.

1233
01:31:00,273 --> 01:31:05,006
No! There is no proof whatsoever
that God was in that courtroom today.

1234
01:31:05,444 --> 01:31:07,742
No, none whatsoever.

1235
01:31:07,813 --> 01:31:11,408
- We saw Him! We heard Him!
- We did.

1236
01:31:14,053 --> 01:31:17,955
- He made himself and the cards disappear.
- We saw it.

1237
01:31:19,058 --> 01:31:23,324
On the basis of our common experience
here today...

1238
01:31:23,996 --> 01:31:27,591
I can see why you first claimed,
and later maintained...

1239
01:31:27,667 --> 01:31:32,161
that you had seen,
and been in the actual presence of...

1240
01:31:33,406 --> 01:31:34,406
God.

1241
01:31:34,874 --> 01:31:39,834
And for that reason,
your remarks to the Rev. Williams...

1242
01:31:39,912 --> 01:31:42,380
could be regarded as a divine assignment.

1243
01:31:43,349 --> 01:31:47,911
I shall rule, therefore,
that the charge of slander be dismissed.

1244
01:31:48,921 --> 01:31:49,921
Sam!

1245
01:31:51,023 --> 01:31:54,186
Now, if, as you also claim...

1246
01:31:54,260 --> 01:31:57,957
it is God's opinion...

1247
01:31:58,197 --> 01:32:02,224
that we should all make
our own decisions...

1248
01:32:02,301 --> 01:32:04,895
and abide by them accordingly...

1249
01:32:04,971 --> 01:32:08,839
then I must also rule
that on the basis of the evidence...

1250
01:32:12,878 --> 01:32:16,041
or rather the lack of it...

1251
01:32:16,415 --> 01:32:19,578
that as much as we all may think...

1252
01:32:19,652 --> 01:32:22,348
that what we saw here today was real...

1253
01:32:23,456 --> 01:32:27,415
God did not, in fact,
appear here before us.

1254
01:32:30,896 --> 01:32:34,730
You may, of course,
appeal to a higher court.

1255
01:32:36,736 --> 01:32:38,761
We heard from the highest court.

1256
01:32:41,907 --> 01:32:43,238
Thank you.

1257
01:32:44,076 --> 01:32:47,876
- Good-bye, Mister Slavic.
- And Jer, we'll send you your picture.

1258
01:32:49,482 --> 01:32:51,109
- Would you do that?
- Sure.

1259
01:32:51,183 --> 01:32:52,183
Thank you.

1260
01:34:37,723 --> 01:34:38,917
Hello?

1261
01:34:39,792 --> 01:34:41,953
- Where are you?
- Turn around.

1262
01:34:50,503 --> 01:34:52,266
How do you like it?

1263
01:34:52,338 --> 01:34:56,035
I'm going on a trip
to spend a little time with animals.

1264
01:34:56,342 --> 01:35:00,335
I like animals, and sometimes
I don't spend enough time with them.

1265
01:35:01,147 --> 01:35:04,981
- We failed, didn't we?
- What are you talking? We did terrific.

1266
01:35:05,317 --> 01:35:09,754
I gave a message of encouragement,
you passed it along, now we'll see.

1267
01:35:10,256 --> 01:35:13,851
You did good. We both did good.
We're covered.

1268
01:35:14,126 --> 01:35:15,957
You think anybody got the message?

1269
01:35:16,028 --> 01:35:19,122
Do you think we have enough apples
in the world?

1270
01:35:19,498 --> 01:35:20,498
Apples?

1271
01:35:20,599 --> 01:35:23,932
We got all the apples we need.
You're Johnny Appleseed.

1272
01:35:24,003 --> 01:35:28,804
You drop a few seeds, and you move on.
If the seeds are good, they'll take root.

1273
01:35:29,208 --> 01:35:31,768
I gave you great seeds, the best.

1274
01:35:32,077 --> 01:35:33,601
I lost my job, you know.

1275
01:35:34,346 --> 01:35:37,406
There are other cities, other supermarkets.

1276
01:35:37,483 --> 01:35:39,212
Everybody thinks I'm a nut.

1277
01:35:39,585 --> 01:35:44,045
Galileo, Pasteur, Einstein, Columbus.

1278
01:35:44,423 --> 01:35:47,017
You're in good company. Hold on.

1279
01:35:50,095 --> 01:35:51,687
Better be going.

1280
01:35:52,097 --> 01:35:54,463
- Aren't you coming back?
- No.

1281
01:35:54,667 --> 01:35:58,228
- Ever?
- When ever comes, we'll see.

1282
01:35:58,637 --> 01:36:02,266
Sometimes, now and then...

1283
01:36:03,442 --> 01:36:04,909
couldn't we just talk?

1284
01:36:04,977 --> 01:36:08,208
I'll tell you what. You talk, I'll listen.
